#15 — Smart Home Device Sound Confusion Suppression

Summary

The invention detects when media content, such as a movie, TV show, video, game, advertisement, or music, contains a sound that matches or resembles notification sounds used by smart devices present in the user’s smart home environment.

These sounds may include a smartphone ringtone, smartwatch alert, smart doorbell chime, washing machine completion tone, microwave beep, oven timer, refrigerator alert, smart speaker notification, security camera alert, robot vacuum sound, baby monitor alert, or other IoT device sounds.

When a matching or similar sound is detected in the media, the system selectively mutes, reduces, replaces, delays, spatially shifts, labels, or modifies only that sound so the user does not mistake media audio for a real smart-home device event. The remaining media audio continues normally.

Concise Novelty

The novelty lies in detecting media sounds that resemble notification or alert sounds of smart devices present in a user’s smart home environment, and selectively modifying only those confusing sounds in the media to prevent false user responses while preserving the rest of the audio experience.